The paper discusses a new approach to database indexing, which is a core topic in computer science databases (cs.DB). The proposed approach focuses on reducing storage overhead and maintenance latency, which are also important topics in data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of histograms for summarizing data, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and compression (cs.CR).
